        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p5",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 3161,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "This submission is made by the Coalition for Open Digital Ecosystems (\"CODE\") in the context of the public consultation by the European Commission (the \"Commission\") on the Digital Fairness Act (\"DFA\").",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s2",
          "section_path": [
            "Coalition for Open Digital Ecosystems",
            "1. Introduction"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 31,
          "char_len": 202
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p6",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 3823,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Openness of digital ecosystems is foundational to consumer choice in digital markets, and consumer choice is foundational to digital fairness in the EU. The freedom to choose devices, applications and services must remain a priority for the Commission. However, in this submission, CODE outlines how the challenges identified by the Commission's call for evidence can be exhaustively addressed by enforcing existing EU rules which directly support the objectives of the Consumer Agenda 2025–2030 without the need for new unnecessary legislative instruments.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s2",
          "section_path": [
            "Coalition for Open Digital Ecosystems",
            "1. Introduction"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 82,
          "char_len": 557
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p7",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Design Patterns",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "Misleading design practices undermine consumers' ability to make free and informed choices in the digital ecosystem."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 9392,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Misleading design practices undermine consumers' ability to make free and informed choices in the digital ecosystem. These practices are found on mobile devices, desktop environments and emerging interfaces such as XR and wearables. They obstruct or manipulate users' ability to choose and retain preferred digital services (such as browsers, search engines, and messaging apps) through anti-competitive design patterns, artificial switching barriers, lack of interoperability, and inconsistent application of consumer rights across device types, thereby undermining genuine consumer choice and fair competition.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s2",
          "section_path": [
            "Coalition for Open Digital Ecosystems",
            "1. Introduction"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 81,
          "char_len": 612
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p8",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Design Patterns",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "When users struggle to customise their digital environment"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 14173,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "When users struggle to customise their digital environment, and are hindered from choosing the digital solutions that best suit their needs and preferences, the result is not just a degraded user experience. It represents a systemic constraint on competition and innovation in the digital age.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s2",
          "section_path": [
            "Coalition for Open Digital Ecosystems",
            "1. Introduction"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 45,
          "char_len": 293
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p9",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Design Patterns",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "dark patterns and other unfair techniques that pressure, deceive and manipulate consumers online"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 6746,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "These issues are among the problems identified in the Commission's Call for Evidence. In particular: preventing traders from using dark patterns and other unfair techniques that pressure, deceive and manipulate consumers online, and increasing competitiveness.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s2",
          "section_path": [
            "Coalition for Open Digital Ecosystems",
            "1. Introduction"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 35,
          "char_len": 260
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p10",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 3956,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "CODE",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s2",
          "section_path": [
            "Coalition for Open Digital Ecosystems",
            "1. Introduction"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 1,
