        },
        "text": "October 2025",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s4",
          "section_path": [
            "2.1 Freedom to set and retain preferred defaults"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 2,
          "char_len": 12
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p24",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Personalisation",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "bringing one's data, services and preferences along."
              },
              {
                "quote": "the ability to move between platforms and ecosystems"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 10787,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "True consumer choice includes the ability to move between platforms and ecosystems, bringing one's data, services and preferences along.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s5",
          "section_path": [
            "2.2 Interoperability and switching as enablers of choice"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 19,
          "char_len": 136
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p25",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Data Portability",
            "topic_source": "new",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "data portability must be technically supported"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 16840,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Content and data portability must be technically supported through synchronisation APIs, migration tools, and interoperable file-sharing protocols.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s5",
          "section_path": [
            "2.2 Interoperability and switching as enablers of choice"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 17,
          "char_len": 147
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p26",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Data Portability",
            "topic_source": "new",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "Data Transfer Initiative"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 21907,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "These tools should be based on open standards and/or certified schemes, such as the Data Transfer Initiative, and available equally to gatekeeper and non-gatekeeper services.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s5",
          "section_path": [
            "2.2 Interoperability and switching as enablers of choice"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 26,
          "char_len": 174
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p27",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Design Patterns",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "Consent mechanisms must be proportionate, informative and clearly designed to empower users, not confuse or discourage them from selecting alternative providers."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 7786,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Consent mechanisms must be proportionate, informative and clearly designed to empower users, not confuse or discourage them from selecting alternative providers.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s5",
          "section_path": [
            "2.2 Interoperability and switching as enablers of choice"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 21,
          "char_len": 161
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p28",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 10461,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Interoperability should be integrated at the ideal interaction point for users, i.e., where competing services are not unnecessarily hindered due to lack of app visibility, default status, or capability.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s5",
          "section_path": [
            "2.2 Interoperability and switching as enablers of choice"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 30,
          "char_len": 203
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p29",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Design Patterns",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "preventing artificial switching barriers."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 18605,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Again, these issues can and should be addressed through existing consumer protection and competition laws. However, should the Commission elect to go ahead with legislative adjustments, it can play a complementary role by establishing user-centric principles that promote seamless configuration of digital environments and objective measures of user satisfaction, focused on user preferences, while preventing artificial switching barriers.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s5",
          "section_path": [
            "2.2 Interoperability and switching as enablers of choice"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 58,
          "char_len": 440
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p30",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 5901,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "To embed meaningful consumer rights and avoid imbalances in digital markets, freedom of choice must apply consistently across all device types - including desktop, mobile, wearables and XR devices - in instances where competing services are being widely distributed on those devices.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s6",
          "section_path": [
            "2.3 Applicability across device form factors"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 40,
          "char_len": 283
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p31",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 4984,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Digital fairness and user empowerment should not be dependent on device form factor, while accounting for user experience, safety and security on a given device format.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s6",
          "section_path": [
            "2.3 Applicability across device form factors"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 26,
          "char_len": 168
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p32",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 5719,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Platforms should support the principles of openness and interoperability across environments.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s6",
          "section_path": [
            "2.3 Applicability across device form factors"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 11,
          "char_len": 93
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p33",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 6024,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Regulation should be complemented by guidance to avoid inadvertent loopholes, which can create an unlevel playing field, undermine enforcement and distort competition across diverse device ecosystems (while taking account of any technical or consumer experience nuances that might exist on a given device).",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s6",
          "section_path": [
            "2.3 Applicability across device form factors"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 43,
          "char_len": 306
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p34",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 4402,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Reinforcing these expectations through guidance to enhance compliance, paired with better enforcement of existing laws, will help ensure that consumer rights are consistent across devices and that no part of the digital ecosystem remains exempt from fairness and openness obligations.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s6",
          "section_path": [
            "2.3 Applicability across device form factors"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 40,
          "char_len": 284
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p35",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 3479,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "October 2025",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s6",
          "section_path": [
            "2.3 Applicability across device form factors"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 2,
          "char_len": 12
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p36",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 3556,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "CODE supports the Commission in its efforts to promote openness and freedom of consumer choice in the digital age. In this context, CODE respectfully requests that the Commission:",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s7",
          "section_path": [
            "3. CODE's suggestions"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 28,
          "char_len": 179
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p37",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 5446,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Acts as a facilitator first, an enforcer second, and a regulator last. Regulators should facilitate the achievement of Europe's policy (like protected and empowered consumers) and economic objectives (like business growth), working alongside businesses to improve compliance by guiding them to comply with the relevant laws. Better compliance improves consumer protection and enables businesses to operate with confidence that their products and services offer \"digital fairness\".",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s7",
          "section_path": [
            "3. CODE's suggestions"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 66,
          "char_len": 480
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p38",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 4210,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "See industry as a critical partner in enhancing common goals of consumer choice, protection and trust. CODE believes that it would be incorrect and a missed opportunity to consider business at large as exploitative and malicious. The EU Institutions have a duty to businesses operating in Europe to pursue this public-private coordination for improved consumer outcomes before any legislative measure can be considered.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s7",
          "section_path": [
            "3. CODE's suggestions"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 63,
          "char_len": 419
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p39",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 3776,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Prioritise addressing the issues set out in this submission through existing tools before considering new legislation, as the solution lies in effective application and harmonisation, not in more regulation.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s7",
          "section_path": [
            "3. CODE's suggestions"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 29,
          "char_len": 207
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p40",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Data Portability",
            "topic_source": "new",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "data portability and cross-platform interoperability"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 11785,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Promotes technical standards schemes for data portability and cross-platform interoperability, especially for smaller innovators.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s7",
          "section_path": [
            "3. CODE's suggestions"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 14,
          "char_len": 129
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p41",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Personalisation",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "focused on user preferences"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 11140,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Establishes user-centric and business-friendly principles that promote seamless configuration of digital environments and objective measures of user satisfaction - focused on user preferences - while preventing artificial switching barriers.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s7",
          "section_path": [
            "3. CODE's suggestions"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 27,
          "char_len": 241
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p42",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 3187,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "CODE remains fully available to assist the Commission in these tasks.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s7",
          "section_path": [
            "3. CODE's suggestions"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 11,
          "char_len": 69
        }
      },
